President Donald J. Trump will meet with Prime Minister Imran Khan of Pakistan at the White House on July 22, 2019. The purpose of the visit is to enhance cooperation between the United States and Pakistan in order to bring peace, stability, and economic prosperity to a region that has experienced significant conflict. The discussions will cover topics such as counterterrorism, defense, energy, and trade, with the aim of fostering a peaceful South Asia and a lasting partnership between the two countries.